Disable FlashAttention-3 (Hopper) build in sgl-kernel for DGX Spark GB10.

Problem:
  FlashAttention-3 (FA3) is a Hopper-architecture-specific kernel
  implementation that uses SM90a-only primitives (wgmma.mma_async, TMA
  with Hopper-specific memory descriptors, persistent warp-specialized
  kernels). It CANNOT run on GB10 (SM121) — the GPU lacks the
  underlying hardware instructions.

  Upstream sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt force-enables FA3 whenever
  CUDA_VERSION >= 12.4 regardless of whether the target arch can
  actually run it. The result: on every sgl-kernel build the entire
  flash-attention Hopper codebase — ~475 translation units under
  hopper/instantiations/flash_fwd_*.cu — is compiled to sm_90a SASS
  that will never execute on this fleet.

  This single FA3 branch is the largest single contributor to
  sgl-kernel build time on DGX Spark, dwarfing the sgl-kernel core
  compilation itself.

Fix:
  Dead-code the `if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.4")`
  branch by wrapping it in `if (FALSE AND ...)`. This:

  1. Keeps the surrounding CMake structure byte-identical so future
     upstream drift is easy to spot in diffs.
  2. Leaves `SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3` at its `option()` default of OFF,
     which causes the downstream `if (SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3)` block
     (around line 416) to skip all flash-attention sources,
     instantiations, and the sm_90a gencode entirely.
  3. No CMake option, no CLI flag — the branch is unconditionally
     dead. Applying this patch means the resulting image has no FA3
     support and sglang's `attention_backend=fa3` will fail at runtime.

Impact on sglang runtime:
  - sgl-kernel's Python `__init__.py` and sglang's attention backend
    discovery rely on `getattr()` / `hasattr()` / try-except probes
    for FA3 availability, so missing FA3 symbols at import time do
    NOT break `import sgl_kernel` or sglang startup. Runtime fallback
    to the triton attention backend is automatic if a caller requests
    fa3 on an unsupported GPU.
  - Our "Winner config" for Qwen3-235B-A22B-NVFP4 and every other
    production profile uses `attention_backend=triton` exclusively —
    no profile depends on FA3. There is no regression on the profiles
    we actually run.
  - THIS PATCH IS OPTIONAL. It is gated by
    --disable-fa3 / APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3=1 in the build flow
    and defaults to OFF so a first-time user gets a "maximally
    compatible" build. Enable it once you have confirmed the sglang
    pod still imports cleanly after a prior build with this patch
    applied.

Expected impact:
  - ~475 flash_fwd_*.cu translation units no longer compiled.
  - sgl-kernel wheel size drops significantly (all FA3 sm_90a cubins
    removed).
  - Build time drops by roughly half of what remains after
    sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch has been applied.

Verification:
  After applying, grep the configured build.ninja (or the raw build
  log) for `hopper/instantiations/flash_fwd` — zero hits means FA3
  was correctly skipped. At runtime, `python -c "import sgl_kernel;
  print(dir(sgl_kernel))"` should still succeed; `attention_backend=fa3`
  in an sglang profile will now fall back to triton with a warning.

Apply to: sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt, inside the Dockerfile builder
stage, BEFORE the sgl-kernel `uv build --wheel` step. This patch
stacks cleanly on top of sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch (patch auto-
offsets the hunk line number since arch-prune shifts lines above).

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.10

--- a/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -242,7 +242,15 @@
     endif()
 endif()
 
-if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.4")
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch: FA3 is Hopper-only (SM90a) and
+# can never run on GB10 (SM121). The upstream block above would force-
+# enable it whenever CUDA >= 12.4 and add a -gencode=sm_90a to the whole
+# sgl-kernel build. Wrapping in `if (FALSE AND ...)` dead-codes the
+# entire branch without touching surrounding structure — SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3
+# then stays at its option() default (OFF) and the FA3 build block further
+# down (~line 416 "if (SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3)") skips all ~475
+# flash-attention hopper/instantiations/*.cu files and the sm_90a gencode.
+if (FALSE AND "${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.4")
     set(SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 ON)
     list(APPEND SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS
         "-gencode=arch=compute_90a,code=sm_90a"
